Get a data frame containing the available SBSs

Source: R/RcppExports.R
MutationEngine-cash-get_SBSs.Rd

This method returns a data frame containing the available SBSs and the corresponding mutation probability. The first column ("Type") describes a mutation in a context, while each of the remaining columns contains the probabilities of the mutations for one of the available SBSs.

Value

A data frame containing the available SBSs.

Examples

# build a mutation engine
m_engine <- build_mutation_engine(setup_code = "demo")
#>
